nl_problem:
# Task: interval_merger
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: merge(self, arg1)

Given an array of intervals where `intervals[i] = [starti, endi]`, merge all overlapping intervals, and return an array of the non-overlapping intervals that cover all the intervals in the input.

Constraints:
- 1 <= intervals.length <= 10^4
- intervals[i].length == 2
- 0 <= starti <= endi <= 10^4
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "merge")
  (signature ((intervals (list (list int)))) (list (list int)))
  (constraints
    (constraint "1 <= length of intervals <= 10^4")
    (constraint "Each interval has a length of 2")
    (constraint "0 <= starti <= endi <= 10^4")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Merge all overlapping intervals and return an array of non-overlapping intervals that cover all the intervals in the input.")
    (rule "Intervals are represented as [start, end].")
    (return "A list of merged intervals where no intervals overlap.")
  )
)
